=== Noun ===
'''maniple''' (''plural:'' [[maniples]])
# ''(rare)'' A [[handful]].
# A [[division]] of the Roman army numbering 60 or 120 men exclusive of officers, any small body of [[soldier]]s; a [[company]].
# Originally, a [[napkin]]; later, an ornamental band or scarf worn upon the left arm as a part of the [[vestment]]s of a priest in the Roman Catholic Church, and sometimes worn in the English Church service.

